annotationA: Rab11, isoform A; Rab11 is a Rab type protein. Rab proteins are ubiquitously expressed family of small monomeric Ras-like GTPases that are key regulators of endomembrane traffiking, regulating exocytosis, endocytosis and membrane recycling processes essential for maintaining various cellular functions
annotationB: Aquaporin; Drip belongs to the MIP/aquaporin family involved in the transport of water across the cell membrane. In addition to its cellular roles, Drip has been implicated in regulating aspects of reproduction and aging
